# tinyproxy FilterDefaultDeny allowlist for the Q&A container.
#
# Distinct from egress/filter: the Q&A pipeline has NO GitHub access. The
# bot's read-only Q&A oracle is the local docs/dev-journal corpus (mounted
# read-only at /app/knowledge), the local Postgres reader role (via the
# db-tunnel sidecar), and the public Leviathan website API.
#
# Mounting GH_TOKEN into Q&A would widen the blast radius of a successful
# prompt-injection inside the container — see plan v6.

# --- Anthropic ------------------------------------------------------------
^api\.anthropic\.com$
^[a-z0-9-]+\.anthropic\.com$

# --- Leviathan public site ------------------------------------------------
# Public news, tags, search APIs — no auth required, read-only.
^leviathannews\.xyz$
^[a-z0-9-]+\.leviathannews\.xyz$

# NOTE: Postgres (read-only `commodore_reader` role on DigitalOcean managed
# DB) is NOT here. It goes through commodore-db-tunnel on the same network.
# NOTE: NO github.com subdomains. Q&A has no business pushing branches or
# reading private repo content live; the docs corpus is mounted instead.
